{"id":"math140-defint210-ap003","cid":"MATH 140","topic":"Applications of Integration","subtopic":"Total accumulated change","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A factory's output rate is O(t) = x^{n} hundred units per hour. Find total output from hour {lo} to hour {hi}.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":1},"n":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":2},"lo":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":2},"hi":{"type":"int","min":3,"max":6}},"answer_expr":"defint210","steps":["Total output = integral from {lo} to {hi} of x^{n} dx = [x^{n+1}/({n+1})] from {lo} to {hi}.","= ({hi_pow} - {lo_pow}) / ({n+1}) = {answer_defint210} hundred units."],"tags":["business-calculus","accumulated-change","output-rate","integration"]}
